<v Speaker 1>I have from Aber is spelled H-E.

00:02:35.020 --> 00:02:37.580
<v Speaker 1>Just like C from Saber is spelled S-E.

00:02:37.580 --> 00:02:43.660
<v Speaker 1>There are the only two verbs that form their I version in this way, in this very irregular way.

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:48.800
<v Speaker 1>So you get se from saber and you get e from.

00:02:48.800 --> 00:02:53.440
<v Speaker 1>Different from saber, all of the versions of aber are irregular

00:02:53.520 --> 00:02:58.000
<v Speaker 1>Now I and we are connected.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.519
<v Speaker 1>We can see how we is the plural of I.

00:03:01.680 --> 00:03:06.800
<v Speaker 1>I and then when I include you and I say we it's like the plural of I.

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:08.959
<v Speaker 1>So I and we are connected.

00:03:08.959 --> 00:03:13.120
<v Speaker 1>So just knowing that if you had to guess what is we have

